                     <interp inst="def2-1519-18390513" type="surname" value="LEWIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1519-18390513" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN LEWIS</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18390513-1519-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390513-1519-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390513-1519-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> stealing, on the <rs id="t18390513-cd-45" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390513-1519-offence-1 t18390513-cd-45"></join>20th of April</rs>, 1 sheet, value 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18390513-name-319" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-319" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-319" type="surname" value="WATTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-319" type="given" value="JAMES EDWARD"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390513-1519-offence-1 t18390513-name-319"></join>James Edward.Watts</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-320" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-320" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-320" type="surname" value="WHATLBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-320" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES WHATLBY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. Robinson, in Nassau-place, Commercial-road. I was at the window between four and five o'clock, on the 20th of April, and I saw the prisoners near Mr.Watts's shop—they walked from the window to the curbstone—I watched, and saw Lyon pull a sheet down from Mr.Watts's window and give it to Lewis, who was at the window—he rolled it up, put it under his arm, and was walking away—I jumped over the counter, crossed the road, and seized him—he said he had the</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183905130036"></xptr>
               <p>sheet given to him—Lyon walked away—another shopman took him, but he was not out of my sight.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-321" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-321" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-321" type="surname" value="FOWLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-321" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY FOWLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr.James Edward Watts—this is his sheet.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Lewis. Q.</hi> Did you hang it out? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> The young man did, either on the edge of the window or on the wall.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-322" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-322" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-322" type="surname" value="WHATLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-322" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES WHATLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. The sheet hung on the window, I believe.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-323" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-323" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-323" type="surname" value="CLAXTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-323" type="given" value="EDMUND"></interp>EDMUND CLAXTON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable K</hi> 122.) I took these prisoners.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Lyon's Defence.</hi> I saw two or three hoys round the window—this sheet was on the pavement—I took it up—I did not know it belonged to the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Lewis's Defence.</hi> I was walking up and down, and this prisoner dropped the sheet—I picked it up, and was going to take it home.</p>
               <p>
